cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with secure communication and information theory, which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The presence of an eavesdropper and the need for secrecy also suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a likely sub-category. The use of side information and the characterization of rate-equivocation regions suggest that cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and the theoretical analysis of the problem suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as well.
